      "id": "maintenance",
      "title": "Maintenance Basics",
      "cards": [
        "Test smoke and CO detectors monthly \u2014 press the button until it beeps.",
        "Check your HVAC filter monthly. Replace it every 60\u201390 days, or sooner if it looks gray or clogged. A clean filter protects your air quality and your system.",
        "Check under sinks and around toilets monthly for drips or moisture. A slow leak caught early prevents mold and costly damage.",
        "Clean your dryer lint trap after every load. Once a year, check that the vent duct behind the dryer is clear \u2014 a clogged duct is a fire hazard.",
        "Vacuum the coils behind or under your refrigerator twice a year to keep it running efficiently and extend its life.",
        "Keep vents and air returns unblocked by furniture, rugs, or stored items.",
        "Replace smoke and CO detector batteries once a year \u2014 changing them when the clocks change is an easy way to remember.",
        "Inspect caulking around your tub and shower annually. Reseal any cracks to keep water from getting into walls."
